## Summary of Testing Results

### Test: Line Break Preservation in List Items

**Steps Performed:**
1. ✅ Navigated to **Toolbar > Basics** in the left navigation
2. ✅ Added an **unordered list** using the toolbar's bullet list button
3. ✅ Typed "First line of list item", pressed **Shift+Enter** (line break), typed "Second line after line break"
4. ✅ Switched to **Source mode** - the Markdown showed:
   ```
   - First line of list item
   
   
     Second line after line break
   ```
5. ✅ Selected all (Cmd+A) and copied (Cmd+C) the source code
6. ✅ Switched to **Rich text mode**, selected all and deleted (Cmd+A, Delete)
7. ✅ Switched to **Source mode**, pasted the copied content (Cmd+V)
8. ✅ Switched back to **Rich text mode** to verify

**Bug Found: LINE BREAK NOT PRESERVED** 🐛

When switching back to Rich text mode after pasting the Markdown, the list item that originally had:
```
• First line of list item
  Second line after line break
```
(with a line break between)

...was displayed as:
```
• First line of list itemSecond line after line break
```
(with NO line break - the text was concatenated without any separator)

The Source mode after the round-trip also shows the two text parts merged on one line: `- First line of list itemSecond line after line break`

This is a **functional bug** where the line break (newline character) within a list item is lost during the copy-paste cycle through Source mode.

